# ⚠️ DEPLOYMENT CHECKLIST - READ BEFORE EVERY DEPLOY

**This is the sequence. Do NOT skip or reorder.**

## Step 1: BACKUP (MANDATORY)
```bash
bash /Users/rk/clawd/backup-full-site.sh
```
- [ ] Script runs without errors
- [ ] Output shows ✅ for all directories + HTML files
- [ ] Backup folder created in `/Users/rk/clawd/_BACKUPS/[TODAY]/`
- [ ] Backup includes: flavorgalaxy/ (with images), rob-kremers-portfolio/ (with everything), root-html/
- [ ] File count in output (should be 80+)
- [ ] Total backup size shown (should be 20-30MB)

## Step 2: GIT COMMIT
```bash
cd /Users/rk/clawd && git add [files] && git commit -m "..." && git push origin main
```
- [ ] All changes staged
- [ ] Commit message is clear & specific
- [ ] Push successful (no auth errors)

## Step 3: VERIFY CHANGES LOCALLY
- [ ] Open the HTML file in browser (or web_fetch)
- [ ] Verify content looks correct
- [ ] Check all images load
- [ ] Test responsive design if possible

## Step 4: DEPLOY TO VERCEL
```bash
cd /Users/rk/clawd && vercel deploy --prod --token [TOKEN] --yes
```
- [ ] Build completes without errors
- [ ] "Aliased" message appears (shows it went to production)
- [ ] Deployment took <2 minutes (red flag if longer)

## Step 5: VERIFY LIVE SITE
- [ ] Visit the live URL (e.g., robkremers.com/flavorgalaxy)
- [ ] Hard refresh (Cmd+Shift+R)
- [ ] Check images load
- [ ] Spot-check content matches what you deployed

## Step 6: DOCUMENT
- [ ] Update MEMORY.md with what changed
- [ ] Note date, page, changes made
- [ ] Done ✅

---

## Red Flags (STOP & INVESTIGATE)

🚨 If ANY of these happen:
- Backup script fails or missing files
- Git push rejected (check for secrets or merge conflicts)
- Vercel build errors (don't override, fix locally first)
- Live site shows old content (clear cache, check vercel.json routing)
- Images are broken (check relative paths, file locations)
- 404 errors on the page (check vercel.json rewrites)

**IF ANYTHING GOES WRONG: RESTORE FROM BACKUP**
1. Check `/Users/rk/clawd/_BACKUPS/` for the last known good version
2. Copy it back to the live location
3. Commit & deploy again
4. Only then debug what went wrong

